\binom 42=\frac{4\cdot3}{2\cdot1}=6
2
9
\binom92=\frac{9\cdot8}{2\cdot1}=36
\frac{\text{ the number of favourable cases }}{\text{  the number of possible cases }}=\frac{6}{36}=\frac16
\frac{\binom52}{\binom92}=\frac5{18}
\frac16+\frac5{18}=\frac49
\frac4{4+5}=\frac49
\frac{4-1}{4+5-1}=\frac38
\frac49\cdot\frac38=\frac16
\frac5{4+5}\frac{5-1}{4+5-1}=\frac5{18}
{9\choose 2}=36
5\cdot 4=20
36-20=16
{16\over 36}={4\over 9}
